                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, July 28 (PTI): A Class IX student today allegedly fired at his schoolmate with an air-pistol during a fight in a south Delhi school.          
	Gaurav Yadav, a Class VIII student, suffered minor injuries and was taken to AIIMS trauma centre. He was discharged later. The incident took place around 9am when the teenager opened fire using a 0.22 bore air-pistol when two groups of students clashed in the playground, a senior police official said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court on Wednesday issued notice to BJP MP Varun Gandhi on a petition filed by his uncle and Congress candidate from Pilibhit V.M. Singh for allegedly making defamatory remarks during the 2009 Lok Sabha elections. Singh had alleged that Varun made remarks linking him to Pakistans ISI and working for a separate state of Khalistan.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): The Kerala government has decided to take up with the Centre its demand for granting the classical language status to Malayalam, minister for education and culture M.A. Baby told the Assembly on Wednesday.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Balaji Telefilms, the producers of Once Upon A Time In Mumbai, on Wednesday agreed to issue a statement that the film is not based on the life of alleged smuggler Haji Mastan, paving the way for its release on July 30.
                                                                                                                                              
